definition.value: A type of repetitive behavior in which the affected individual repeatedly waves the hands and/or arms rhythmically.
An unusually happy demeanor over time, which can also be observed during inappropriate situations that should, for example, cause distress, fear, or anger.
Movement-based tics affecting discrete muscle groups.
